Ad Text:
About the Role

In this role you will be responsible for the design, implementation, improvement and support of TMBL Enterprise Data Warehouse and Analytics Solutions.

You will also liaise with Business Analysts and business users to gather business requirements and be involved in all stages of data development for BI & Analytics project work i.e. requirements gathering, solution design (ETL & Data modelling), data transformation, system testing, integration testing and deployment.

You will recommend improvements to provide optimum solutions and stay updated with business operations and business intelligence processes. You will conduct training programs and knowledge transfer sessions to junior developers and business users when needed.

This role is a 12 month fixed term contract.

Key responsibilities:

Gathers, research, and analyses data to develop insightful conclusions and generates solutions to address user needs.
Designs, develops and troubleshoots ETL processes using SSIS and DataStage along with detailed estimation and organises the tasks-based priority from the business.
Models New Data Assets in the Enterprise Data warehouse platform aligned to 3NF & Dimensional modelling.
Designs SQL Server 2008/2012/2016 data models to support business intelligence systems within a data warehouse environment.
Develops SQL Server stored procedures, functions, views and triggers to support business intelligence functions.
Designs and develops Dashboard reports using QlikView.  
About You

Relevant tertiary qualifications
Strong experience in SQL server development, ETL development using data driven frameworks or any industry ETL tools
Prior experience in the development and support of large Enterprise Data Warehouse (highly desirable) 
Skills and Qualifications:

Experience with relational and dimensional data modelling and analysis
Strong analytical and problem solving skills
Experience working in Azure Data Platform, Big Data Platform
Experience with CICD pipelines for data engineering with Github/Azure Dev ops
About us:

Teachers Mutual Bank Limited is one of the largest mutual banks in Australia. We are a globally-recognised socially responsible bank with profit-for-purpose as our business model and philosophy. At our Bank, social responsibility is built-in, not bolted on and drives our business practices, people, and products.
  
We are proud to serve some of Australia’s essential workers in education, emergency services and healthcare. We believe they deserve a bank that does good for their community.
  
We have been named one of the World’s Most Ethical Companies for ten years in a row and are a Certified B Corp Bank.

Our employees embrace our organisation’s values of passion, advocacy and sustainability, and contribute to a diverse and inclusive workplace culture founded on mutual respect, equality and a focus on striving to deliver exceptional member service.
  
We are an Employer of Choice, promote Diversity and Inclusion, and follow EEO principles by appointing on merit. We work under a hybrid working model to provide flexibility in the workplace. For more information about working conditions as well as our employee value proposition, please visit the careers page on our website at www.tmbank.com.au or find us on LinkedIn!

How to apply:

Please click the APPLY button and follow the prompts.
  
For a confidential conversation, please contact Jobs@tmbank.com.au

By applying you agree to cooperate fully in those procedures and understand that an offer is subject to the satisfactory outcome of those checks, at the discretion of Teachers Mutual Bank Ltd.
